articles.headline: Rockets' Kevin Durant eighth ever to reach 31,000 points
articles.description: Rockets star Kevin Durant, who entered Friday as the NBA's No. 8 all-time leading scorer, reached the 31,000-point milestone in the first quarter against the Suns.

articles.headline: Jake LaRavia shows off shirt featuring Anthony Edwards' 'Who is No. 12?' quip
articles.description: Anthony Edwards' courtside commentary and Jake LaRavia's 27-point night turned a short-handed matchup into an instant classic back in late October.

articles.headline: Knicks' OG Anunoby back vs. Jazz after nine-game absence
articles.description: Knicks forward OG Anunoby, who missed the past nine games with a left hamstring strain, was back in the starting lineup Friday against the Jazz.

articles.headline: Giannis Antetokounmpo to require close to 4 weeks of recovery, Doc Rivers says
articles.description: Bucks coach Doc Rivers said he expects star Giannis Antetokounmpo to require closer to four weeks to recover from the strained right calf he suffered Wednesday night.

images.name: Will Giannis demand a trade from the Bucks?
images.caption: Brian Windhorst joins "Get Up" to discuss if Giannis's recent calf injury might impact future trade discussions.

articles.headline: LeBron James, Luka Doncic sit out for Lakers at Celtics
articles.description: The Lakers will be without both LeBron James and Luka Doncic for Friday night's game in Boston against the Celtics.
